Text Editing actions


%!includeconf: t2t.conf
%!options(html): --outfile ../doc/xix_ref_acttxt.html

~B[Reference xix_ref.html]→[Main Window xix_ref_mainwin.html]→
[Menu Actions xix_ref_actions.html]→[Edit Menu xix_ref_actedit.html]~E

In general, ~X's editors support all the usual keyboard actions, such as
~KCtrl+C~E to copy text and ~KCtrl+V~E to paste text~~~see the
[Edit→Clipboard actions xix_ref_act_e_clip.html]. The usual editing and
selecting actions are supported, for example, ~KBackspace~E to delete
the previous character, and selecting text with the mouse or by pressing
the ~KLeft~E or ~KRight~E arrow keys with the ~KShift~E key held
down~~~see the ~{#keypresses table at the end}.

And if you haven't yet saved or left an editor, you can undo and redo
your edits using the [Edit→Undo and Redo actions xix_ref_act_e_do.html].

In addition, the ~KTerm~E and ~KPages~E editors support text styling
such as **bold** and //italics//.

And the ~KTerm~E editor also supports //completion//, that is, as you
type in a word, wherever possible, ~X shows suggestions for what the word
you have started typing might be in the
[Main Window Suggestions Panel xix_ref_panel_sug.html]. The suggestions
are based on the spelling dictionary, including any words you have added
to this index's custom dictionary. (~X also supports automatic
replacements in the ~KTerm~E editor~~~sometimes called a //glossary//
function; see the [Spelling→Auto Replace action xix_ref_act_l_auto.html].)

